                           <locus target="#84rb">f. 84rb</locus>
                           <desc type="DonationNote">Donation note.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#84rb">84rb</locus>: ˂…˃ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘቅዱስ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ˂…˃፡ ዘወሀቦ፡
                              ወልደ፡ ሚካኤል፡ አቡሁ፡ ተስፋ፡ ማርያም፡ ዓመተ፡ ሚካኤል።</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">
                              <locus target="#84rb">84rb</locus>: [This] book is of St Michael ˂…˃,
                              which Walda Mikāʾel donated. His father is Tasfā Māryām [and his … is]
                              ʿĀmata Mikāʾel.</q>
                           <note> The note is written in vivid scarlet, in the same hand as Additio
                              1 and the names in the supplication formulas. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#84va">f. 84va</locus>
                           <desc type="DonationNote">Donation note. </desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#84va">84va</locus>: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘመድኃኒ፡ ዓለም፡ አዲግራት፡ ዘወሀቦ፡
                              ዳግማዊ፡ ዘመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ወምስለ፡ ብእሲቱ፡ ዓመተ፡ ድንግል፡ ከመ፡ ይኵኖሙ፡ መርሃ፡ ለመንግስተ፡
                              ሰማያት።</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">
                              This book is of ʾAddigrāt Madḫāni
                              ʿĀlam which Dāgǝmāwi Za-Manfas Qǝddus donated and his wife is ʿĀmata
                              Dǝngǝl, so that it might be for them a guide to the Kingdom of Heaven. </q>
                           <note> The note is written in vivid scarlet, but in a finer hand,
                              different from that of Additiones 1-2. It states that the Ms. was
                              donated by Dāgǝmāwi Za-Manfas Qǝddus whose wife is ʾĀmata Dǝngǝl. The
                              note states that the Ms. was donated by Dāgǝmāwi Za-Manfas Qǝddus and
                              his wife ʾĀmata Dǝngǝl. The note is written in the same hand as the
                              donation note in Ms. AMM-001 (s. Additio 2) and, most probably, the
                              donation note in Mss. AMM-005, AMM-006. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The title of the work, ግንዘት, is written in blue pen:
                              <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>.
 - Tamallas-sign indicating the
                           place where the omission, written in the margin, belong: <locus target="#58rb">58rb</locus>.
 - Corrections written interlineally:
                              <locus target="#10rb">10rb</locus>, 10vb, 26ra, 38va, 71rb, 76va,
                           79ra.
 - Space for rubricated names left unfilled in the supplication
                           formulas: <locus target="#14ra">14ra</locus>, 64v.
 - A note,
                           probably the original ownership or donation note, has been erased from
                              <locus target="#84rb">84rb</locus>.
 - A note, probably concerning
                           donation, has been blotted out from <locus target="#84va">84va</locus>.
 - Pen trial: <locus target="#10r">10r</locus>.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Notes in the upper margin encircled with broken
                              lines, referring to the content: fols. 11r, 13r, 23v, 25v, 27v, 29r,
                              39r, 39v, 40r, 42r, 53v, 55r, 56r-v, 57v, 58v, 59r, 60r, 62v, 64v,
                              67r, 69r, 70v.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
