               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0064AMM">ʿĀddigrāt Madḫāne ʿĀlam</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1800" notAfter="1900">The Patriarch of Alexandria ( liqa
                        ṗaṗṗasǝnä) ʾabbā Mārqos (in tenure ) and Metropolitan (ṗaṗṗasǝnä) ʾabbā
                        Matewos (in tenure ) and King Yoḥannǝs (r. ) are mentioned in the
                        supplication formulas on <locus target="#40rb">40rb</locus>.</origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>The name of the original donor has been erased from the supplication
                     formulas and replaced with the names of Walda Mikāʾel, Tasfā Māryām and Walatta
                     Mikāʾel (e.g., <locus target="#14vb">14vb</locus>, 38ra, 52vb), Walda Yoḥannǝs
                     (e.g., <locus target="#61vb">61vb</locus>), Gabra Ḥǝywat (e.g., <locus target="#62ra">62ra</locus>), Kǝnfa Mikāʾel (e.g., <locus target="#61va">61va</locus>). The first three names are also mentioned in Additiones 1 and
                     2. 
 All the names have been added by a secondary hand, in vivid
                     scarlet.
 According to Additio 3, the Ms. was donated by Dāgǝmāwi Za-Manfas
                     Qǝddus and his wife ʾĀmata Dǝngǝl. Dāgǝmāwi Za-Manfas Qǝddus might be
                     identified with the second son of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8265Sabagadi">daǧǧāzmāč Sabāgādis</persName> (1770-1831), <persName role="donor" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4996hagosSa">Ḫagos</persName> (d.
                     1831). The identification is based on Additiones 1 and 2 in Ms. FBM-002. He
                     also donated Ms. FBM-009.</provenance>
               </history>
